Burna Boy on the red carpet at the 2021 BET Awards | Image: The Hollywood Reporter/Twitter Burna Boy has won the Best International Act Award at the 2021 BET Awards ceremony held last night at the Microsoft Theater in Los Angeles. This is the third win in the category for the “African Giant” singer who took home the award in 2019 and 2020. Burna Boy beat fellow Nigerian, Wizkid, and Tanzania’s Diamond Platnumz to the award. Others nominated in the category are Aya Nakamura (France), Emicida (Brazil), Headie One (United Kingdom), Young T & Bugsey (United Kingdom) and Youssopha (France).   A post shared by BET Africa (@bet_africa)  Read More:
